title: Worked Solution
text:
To convert meters per second to kilometers per hour, we need to multiply by $$3.6$$.
So, the speed of the car in kilometers per hour is:
$$33$$ $$ rac{m}{s}$$ × $$3.6$$ $$=$$ $$118.8$$ $$ rac{km}{h}$$
Therefore, the car is traveling at a speed of $$118.8$$ kilometers per hour.
